  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Chop your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into small cubes</p><p>Zest <strong>half</strong> your<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><strong>lemon[s] </strong>(try to grate lightly with a micro-plane or sharp box grater and avoid grating the white pith, as this is very bitter)</p><p>Deseed your <strong>sweet pointed pepper[s] </strong>(scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and chop into chunks</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/sweet-pepper-truffled-honey-and-goats-cheese-montadito/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine <strong>half</strong> your <strong>dried thyme</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) and your <strong>ground smoked paprika</strong> in a<strong> </strong>large bowl<strong> </strong>with the <strong>cubed potatoes</strong>, <strong>lemon zest</strong>, a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and <strong>pepper </strong>– these are your<strong> marinated potatoes</strong></p><p>Transfer the <strong>marinated potatoes</strong> to a <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined baking tray (or two!) and put the tray[s] in the oven for 25 min or until golden and crisp – these are your <strong>smoky, lemon & thyme potatoes</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/sweet-pepper-truffled-honey-and-goats-cheese-montadito/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Slice your <strong>ciabatta[s]</strong> in half, then add the <strong>ciabatta halves</strong> to one side of a separate baking tray (or two!) with a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>chopped pepper</strong> to the other side of the tray[s] with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 10 min or until the ciabatta is golden and crisp and the peppers are tender – these are your <strong>crisp breads and roasted sweet pointed peppers</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/sweet-pepper-truffled-honey-and-goats-cheese-montadito/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, combine <strong>half </strong>your <strong>honey</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) and the juice of <strong>half</strong> your<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><strong>lemon[s]</strong> in a large bowl with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and<strong> pepper </strong>– this is your<strong> dressing</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>tomato[es]</strong> roughly</p><p>Wash your <strong>salad</strong> and pat it dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Add the <strong>salad</strong> and <strong>chopped tomato</strong> to the bowl and toss – this is your <strong>dressed salad</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/sweet-pepper-truffled-honey-and-goats-cheese-montadito/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Crumble your <strong>goats' cheese</strong> into small pieces</p><p>Peel and chop your <strong>garlic </strong>in half</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/sweet-pepper-truffled-honey-and-goats-cheese-montadito/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the ciabatta is golden and crisp, remove the tray[s] from the oven and set aside to cool slightly, then rub the sliced-side of the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>garlic </strong>over it (not a fan of raw garlic? Only use a little!)</p><p>Top with the <strong>roasted sweet pointed peppers</strong>, then the <strong>crumbled</strong> <strong>goats' cheese</strong></p><p>Drizzle over the<strong> remaining honey</strong>, your <strong>truffle oil </strong>(not a fan of truffle oil? Just add a little!) and the<strong> remaining dried thyme </strong>– these are your <strong>toasts</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/sweet-pepper-truffled-honey-and-goats-cheese-montadito/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the potatoes are nearly ready, put the tray[s] with the toasts in the oven and cook for 2-3 min or until slightly melted – these are your <strong>sweet pepper, truffled honey & goats' cheese montaditos</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/sweet-pepper-truffled-honey-and-goats-cheese-montadito/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>sweet pepper, truffled honey & goats' cheese montadito </strong>with the<strong> dressed salad </strong>and<strong> smoky, lemon & thyme potatoes </strong>to the side</p><p>Cut the <strong>remaining lemon</strong> into 1 wedge per person</p><p>Garnish with a <strong>lemon wedge</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
